results.name: Number of strict integer partitions of n not containing 1 or any prime indices of the parts.
comment: A prime index of n is a number m such that prime(m) divides n. The multiset of prime indices of n is row n of A112798.
example: The a(2) = 1 through a(17) = 12 strict integer partitions (A...H = 10...17):
2  3  4  5  6   7   8  9   A   B    C   D    E    F    G    H
A2  B2   B3   B4   D3   C5
An example for n = 60 is (19,14,13,7,5,2), with prime indices:
None of these prime indices {1,3,4,6,8} belong to the partition, as required.
xref: The subset version is A324742, with maximal case is A324763. The non-strict version is A324757. The Heinz number version is A324761. An infinite version is A304360.
